<br>
I find the whole thing an interesting theory, but haven't gone so far as to dedicate my life to it.  It has to make you wonder though, is the question really why are &quot;we&quot; here, or is it why is it all here? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucraeven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Craeven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/01 11:50:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=281.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question for you....</span><hr size=1> Amost all of us at one point, or perhaps many points in our lives are faced with these questions.  Is there a God ? Why are we here ? etc etc.<br>
<br>
